  <h1>Terms and Conditions for Property Rental</h1>
  
  <h2>1. Booking and Payment:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>To secure your reservation, a non-refundable deposit of 50% of the total rental fee is required at the time of booking.</li>
    <li>The remaining balance must be paid 1-5 days prior to the check-in date.</li>
    <li>Payments can be made via Zelle, Venmo, Cash, or Wire Transfer.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>2. Check-in and Check-out:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Check-in time is at 3PM on the day of arrival.</li>
    <li>Check-out time is at 12PM on the day of departure.</li>
    <li>Early check-in or late check-out may be accommodated based on availability and must be requested in advance.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>3. Cancellation and Refunds:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>In the event of cancellation, the initial deposit is non-refundable.</li>
    <li>Cancellations made 2 weeks prior to the check-in date will be refunded 100% of the total rental fee.</li>
    <li>No refunds will be provided for cancellations made within 1 week of the check-in date.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>4. Property Usage:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>The property is to be used solely for vacation purposes and not for any commercial activities.</li>
    <li>The maximum number of guests allowed is 24. Exceeding this limit may result in additional charges or termination of the rental agreement.</li>
    <li>The property is strictly non-smoking. Smoking is only allowed in designated outdoor areas.</li>
    <li>Pets are allowed, and Kennels are available for your use. Please keep your pet on a leash when outside.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>5. Damages and Liability:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>The renter is responsible for any damages caused to the property or its contents during the stay.</li>
    <li>The renter agrees to indemnify and hold the property owner harmless from any liabilities, injuries, or claims arising from the renter's use of the property.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>6. Noise and Disturbances:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Guests are expected to respect the neighbors and keep noise levels to a minimum, especially during nighttime hours.</li>
    <li>Parties or events that may cause excessive noise or disturbance are not permitted without prior written consent.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>7. Maintenance and Repairs:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>The property owner will make reasonable efforts to ensure that all amenities and appliances are in working order.</li>
    <li>The renter must promptly report any maintenance or repair issues to the property owner to allow for timely resolution.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>8. Governing Law and Disputes:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>This agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of California.</li>
    <li>Any disputes arising from this rental agreement shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of California.</li>
  </ol>

